Generic single-database configuration for app-ask-ai.

This Alembic setup manages database migrations for the app-ask-ai FastAPI application.

Key Features:

- App-specific version table: alembic_version_ask_ai
- Namespace prefix: ask*ai* for all tables
- Upgrade-only migrations (no automatic downgrades)
- Integration with app settings via POSTGRES\_\* environment variables

Usage:
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-status # Check migration status
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-upgrade # Apply pending migrations
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-create MSG='description' # Create new migration

See Makefile.Alembic for full command reference.

Important Rules:

1. All table names must use 'ask*ai*' prefix (e.g., ask_ai_conversations, ask_ai_messages)
2. All indexes must use 'ix*ask_ai*' prefix
3. All foreign keys must use 'fk*ask_ai*' prefix
4. Migrations are upgrade-only (downgrade functions contain only 'pass')
5. Use POSTGRES\_\* system environment variables (no .env files)
